[[File:Bandeira-macaparana.gif|thumb|180px|right|Macaparana Flag]] '''Macaparana''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located {{convert|120|km|abbr=off}} away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. It has an estimated ({{As of|2009|alt=as of [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|2009]]}}) population of 24.031 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State – [[Pernambuco]] * Region – [[Zona da Mata (coastal)|Zona da mata Pernambucana]] * Boundaries – [[Paraiba]] state ('''N''' and '''W'''); [[São Vicente Ferrer, Pernambuco|São Vicente Ferrer]] and [[Vicência]] ('''S'''); [[Timbaúba]] ('''E'''). * Area – {{convert|126.35|km2|2|lk=on|abbr=off}} * Elevation – {{convert|350|m|ft|lk=out|abbr=off}} * Hidrography – [[Goiana River]] * Vegetation – [[Subcaducifólia]] forest * Clima – Hot tropical and humid * Annual average temperature – {{convert|23.1|C|F|1|lk=on|abbr=off}} * Distance to [[Recife]] – {{convert|120|km|mi|lk=out|abbr=off}}
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Macaparana''' are based in industry, [[commerce]] and [[agribusiness]], especially [[sugarcane]], [[banana]]s; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]] and [[poultry]].
